summary: A test suite that validates the internal behavior of a parsing system. It prepares the test environment, runs a series of unit tests covering module backtracking, handling of invalid module sources, loading of local, inner‑registry and nested modules (including duplicate detection), processing of malformed output blocks, support for type variables, and specific TensorFlow parser functionality, then cleans up after each test.
business_intent: Guarantee the correctness and robustness of the parser's core mechanisms by automatically detecting regressions and edge‑case failures, thereby supporting reliable software releases and easier maintenance of the parsing component.
